bids(uint256).details: Will revert if the bid does not exist

params.bidId: The id of the bid to get

checkpoint().details: This function is called every time a new bid is submitted above the current clearing priceIf the auction is over, it returns the final checkpoint

returns._checkpoint: The checkpoint at the current block

params.blockNumber: The block number to get the checkpoint for

claimTokens(uint256).details: Anyone can claim tokens for any bid, the tokens are transferred to the bid owner

claimTokensBatch(address,uint256[]).details: Anyone can claim tokens for bids of the same owner, the tokens are transferred to the ownerA TokensClaimed event is emitted for each bid but only one token transfer will be made

clearingPrice().details: This will be at least as up to date as the latest checkpoint. It can be incremented from calls to `forceIterateOverTicks`Callers MUST ensure that the latest checkpoint is up to date before using this function.Additionally, it is recommended to use this function instead of reading the clearingPrice from the latest checkpoint.

returns._0: The current clearing price in Q96 form

currencyRaised().details: This may be less than the balance of this contract if there are outstanding refunds for biddersBe aware that the latest checkpoint may be out of date

currencyRaisedQ96_X7().details: Most use cases will want to use `currencyRaised()` instead

exitBid(uint256).details: This function can only be used for bids where the max price is above the final clearing price after the auction has ended

exitPartiallyFilledBid(uint256,uint64,ui.details: This function can be used only for partially filled bids. For fully filled bids, `exitBid` must be used

params.lastFullyFilledCheckpointBlock: The last checkpointed block where the clearing price is strictly < bid.maxPrice
params.outbidBlock: The first checkpointed block where the clearing price is strictly > bid.maxPrice, or 0 if the bid is partially filled at the end of the auction

isGraduated().details: The auction is considered graduated if the currency raised is greater than or equal to the required currency raisedBe aware that the latest checkpoint may be out of date

returns._0: bool True if the auction has graduated, false otherwise

lastCheckpointedBlock().details: Be aware that the last checkpointed block may not be up to date, it is recommended      to always call `checkpoint()` before using getter functions

returns._0: The block number of the last checkpoint

latestCheckpoint().details: Be aware that the latest checkpoint may not be up to date, it is recommended      to always call `checkpoint()` before using getter functions

lbpInitializationParams().details: The implementing contract MUST ensure that these values are correct at the time of calling

nextActiveTickPrice().details: This will be equal to the clearingPrice if no ticks have been initialized yet

returns._0: The price of the next active tick
The id of the next bid to be created

submitBid(uint256,uint128,address,bytes).details: It is NOT recommended to use this function unless you are sure that `maxPrice` is already initialized      as this function will iterate through every tick starting from the floor price if it is not.

params.hookData: Additional data to pass to the hook required for validation
params.maxPrice: The maximum price the bidder is willing to pay

params.hookData: Additional data to pass to the hook required for validation
params.maxPrice: The maximum price the bidder is willing to pay
params.prevTickPrice: The price of the previous tick

sweepCurrency().details: Can be called by anyone after the auction has ended

sweepUnsoldTokens().details: This function can only be called after the auction has ended

ticks(uint256).details: The returned tick is not guaranteed to be initialized

params.price: The price of the tick, which must be at a boundary designated by the tick spacing

returns._0: The tick at the given price

totalClearedQ96_X7().details: Most use cases will want to use `totalCleared()` instead
